  "text": "disrupt RNA-binding activity of both RRMs [CITATION_1] . The X-ray crystal structure of UP1 has been determined [CITATION_2] and it shows proper folding of UP1 into two RRMs. The phenyalanines mutated in M(RRM1,2) are solvent exposed, therefore their substitution with acidic residues should not influence the folding of the protein. Neither of these hnRNP A1 mutant proteins could reconstitute the splicing inhibition of the wildtype HIV-1 substrate when added to the depleted extract ( Figure 4B, lanes 11-14) . These results indicate that both the N-terminal RRMs and the C-terminal glycine-rich domain are required for the splicing inhibitory activity of hnRNP A1.",
